Welcome to PiCAST 2.0!
- Setup PiC2.0 - Manual (DO AT YOUR OWN RISK)
----------------------------------------------

Min. Required Features
1). Open a Terminal.
 1*). Type: sudo apt-get update (recommended on new Installs/Get Latest Packages; optional)
 1A). Type: sudo aptitude install -y youtube-dl netcat mplayer
 1B). TYpe: sudo youtube-dl -U (highly recommended as YouTube changes its core dev. often)

Setup Core System
2). Open a Terminal.
 2A). Type: mv /Path-To-PiCAST/PiCAST /home/$USER (Change how desired BUT remember for alias)
 2B). Type: alias pic_ytvid="sh /home/$USER/PiCAST/youtube/yt-videograb.sh"
 2C). Type: alias pic_ytmusic="sh /home/$USER/PiCAST/youtube/yt-musicgrab.sh"
 - DON'T ADD IN 2.0, YET! 2D). Type: alias pic_ytmidori="sh /home/$USER/PiCAST/youtube/yt-midori.sh"
 2E). Type: alias pic_brow-midori="sh /home/$USER/PiCAST/browser/brow-midori.sh"
 *** Note: Change $USER/PATH to where you placed it if different from above.
